"{\"uid\": \"thecitizen.co.tz-tanzania-oped-africa-takes-maasai-mojo-to-the-olympic-games-4709856\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Prime  Team Kenya athletes pose for a selfie during the opening ceremony of 2024 Olympic Games in Paris on Friday night.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12, \"end\": 17, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.513475844985777e-23, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.298762020713265e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ByCharles Onyango-Obbo    An article in the wonderfully quirky Lithuanian art and pop culture magazine Bored Panda, just gave a thumbs up to the uniforms that Kenya's and South Sudan's 2024 Olympics teams wore at the weekend opening ceremony in Paris.\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 225, \"end\": 236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bored_Panda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bored Panda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bored_Panda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bored_Panda\"}, {\"begin\": 281, \"end\": 286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.513475844985777e-23, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 367, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.298762020713265e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The entertaining Bored Panda, which has 100 million unique visitors a month, rated Kenya's uniform as the second best, and South Sudan's as the third best.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 392, \"end\": 403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bored_Panda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bored Panda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bored_Panda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bored_Panda\"}, {\"begin\": 458, \"end\": 463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.513475844985777e-23, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Sierra Leoneans also got a look in for their uniform, with the authors placing them fifth.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 625, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Further down, the Egyptians came in 20th.\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\", \"score\": 0.9999999315141418, \"rank\": 4.5366940829279976e-08, \"text\": \"Egyptians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In common, all the uniforms were created by African designers.\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team Kenya's attire, stunning Maasai-inspired kits, was designed by Nairobi fashion brand Kovu Couture.\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.513475844985777e-23, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7439680051356476e-26, \"text\": \"Nairobi\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Sudan's uniform was designed by Rwandan fashion house Moshions.\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 905, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"British African heritage brand Labrum, founded by Sierra Leonean Foday Dumbuya, designed Team Sierra Leone's uniforms; and Concrete, a menswear fashion brand based in Egypt, designed Team Egypt's uniforms.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 906, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9948467633168409, \"rank\": 0.003061340499889772, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 937, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Labrum_(arthropod_mouthpart)\", \"score\": 0.9801230330464664, \"rank\": 0.010204081632649378, \"text\": \"Labrum\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Labrum_(arthropod_mouthpart)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Labrum_(arthropod_mouthpart)\"}, {\"begin\": 956, \"end\": 970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Leone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.081187979623386e-18, \"text\": \"Sierra Leonean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Leone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Leone\"}, {\"begin\": 1000, \"end\": 1012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Leone\", \"score\": 0.9999997990094218, \"rank\": 2.009905406080336e-07, \"text\": \"Sierra Leone\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Leone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Leone\"}, {\"begin\": 1029, \"end\": 1037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concrete_art\", \"score\": 0.9274084416591303, \"rank\": 0.05149272002238314, \"text\": \"Concrete\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concrete_art\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concrete_art\"}, {\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9572303214998952, \"rank\": 0.04468065565895496, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}, {\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9572303214998952, \"rank\": 0.04468065565895496, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the varied world of East African aesthetics, Kovu Couture and Moshions moved in both opposite and the same directions with their designs.\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1253, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kovu Couture started today and moved back into tradition.\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It said its design was, \\\"celebrating the vibrant colours, traditions, and stories that make our country unique\\\".\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moshions, known for its avant-garde and experimental approach to fashion, harnessed traditional themes and took a look into the future.\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, both paid homage to African tradition.\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was a time when African designers did not get such pride of place.\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"African teams at the Olympics - and Commonwealth Games - looked largely the same; in western suits, ties, and sun hats for men.\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1722, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"score\": 0.9967845896379733, \"rank\": 0.003102917398507767, \"text\": \"Commonwealth Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maasai beads would not only have been considered heathen, but no one would have thought of them.\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1911, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rwanda's Imigongo traditional art which Moshion channels employed, was nearly wiped out in the 1994 genocide against the Tutsi and has only bounced back in the last two decades thanks to a women's cooperative in the eastern part of the country which revived it.\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 2173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1912, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0441351007352651e-16, \"text\": \"Rwanda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda\"}, {\"begin\": 1921, \"end\": 1929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imigongo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imigongo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imigongo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imigongo\"}, {\"begin\": 2033, \"end\": 2038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tutsi\", \"score\": 0.9969662777198505, \"rank\": 0.0030429537565376794, \"text\": \"Tutsi\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tutsi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tutsi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These creative movements, therefore, speak volumes about how Africans see themselves - more vividly as more connected to our history - and at a visceral level, a determination not to disappear.\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has, therefore, been interesting to watch the regionalisation of Maasai art, together with its commercialisation, which has been a longer-running global phenomenon.\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2438, \"end\": 2444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.576672191879865e-29, \"text\": \"Maasai\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Maasai blanket, beads, bracelets and earrings have been at the centre of this diffusion.\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not too long ago while travelling in the northern Uganda towns of Lira, and further northwest in Arua near the border with the Democratic Republic of Congo, I encountered itinerant hawkers of Masaai wares and art.\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2682, \"end\": 2688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.801884402032571e-29, \"text\": \"Uganda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}, {\"begin\": 2698, \"end\": 2702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lira\", \"score\": 0.9843463327655485, \"rank\": 0.013091775437817225, \"text\": \"Lira\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lira\"}, {\"begin\": 2729, \"end\": 2733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arua\", \"score\": 0.9999999998221938, \"rank\": 1.7790919172954136e-10, \"text\": \"Arua\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arua\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arua\"}, {\"begin\": 2824, \"end\": 2830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Masaai\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was impressive how far they had travelled from home.\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2901, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today many African women - including those in the Diaspora - especially those who consider themselves pan-Africanist and progressive, have to pay homage to Maasai culture to look complete.\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 3091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2914, \"end\": 2927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"African women\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 2953, \"end\": 2961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_diaspora\", \"score\": 0.9999663076947227, \"rank\": 3.369344030569328e-05, \"text\": \"Diaspora\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_diaspora\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_diaspora\"}, {\"begin\": 3059, \"end\": 3065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.576672191879865e-29, \"text\": \"Maasai\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Look at their photographs on Instagram, Facebook, and X (Twitter) and there it will be - the photograph with the Maasai headband, or necklace.\", \"from\": 3092, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3121, \"end\": 3130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.384886859393691e-24, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You are a courageous woman receiving an international award for saving a forest, rescuing young girls from human traffickers, or returning wayward boys to society?\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then you show up in London or New York to receive it in a kitenge dress, and Maasai beads around the neck or forehead, otherwise you are \\\"naked\\\".\", \"from\": 3399, \"to\": 3544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3419, \"end\": 3425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999558895, \"rank\": 4.371805360768415e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 3429, \"end\": 3437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999994083737, \"rank\": 5.913182598369929e-10, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 3476, \"end\": 3482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.576672191879865e-29, \"text\": \"Maasai\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why this contemporary love affair with the cultural riches of the Maa people?\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The author Karen Blixen famously (or better infamously) wrote that \\\"A Maasai warrior is a fine sight.\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3635, \"end\": 3647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Blixen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Blixen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Blixen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Blixen\"}, {\"begin\": 3694, \"end\": 3700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.576672191879865e-29, \"text\": \"Maasai\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those young men have, to the utmost extent, that particular form of intelligence which we call chic; daring and wildly fantastical as they seem, they are still unswervingly true to their own nature, and to an [inherent] ideal.\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their style is not an assumed manner, nor an imitation of a foreign perfection; it has grown from the inside and is an expression of the race and its history, and their weapons and finery are as much a part of their being as are a stag's antlers.\\\"\", \"from\": 3953, \"to\": 4200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Maasai are a Kenyan and Tanzanian people.\", \"from\": 4202, \"to\": 4247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4230, \"end\": 4239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.275784701308294e-36, \"text\": \"Tanzanian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because the \\\"anti-tribal\\\" Tanzanians do not include ethnicity in the population census, their population is estimated to be between 430,000 and 500,000.\", \"from\": 4248, \"to\": 4400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Kenya, the Maasai population was reported as numbering 1,189,522 in the 2019 census, so they should be nearing two million.\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4404, \"end\": 4409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.513475844985777e-23, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 4415, \"end\": 4421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.576672191879865e-29, \"text\": \"Maasai\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Colonialists in Kenya and Tanzania made life hard for the Maasai.\", \"from\": 4529, \"to\": 4594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4545, \"end\": 4550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.513475844985777e-23, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 4555, \"end\": 4563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.585066202956951e-31, \"text\": \"Tanzania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They introduced diseases like syphilis to reduce the Maasai population and East Coast Fever to decimate their cattle herds.\", \"from\": 4595, \"to\": 4718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4625, \"end\": 4633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syphilis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.93831370057835e-20, \"text\": \"syphilis\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syphilis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syphilis\"}, {\"begin\": 4648, \"end\": 4654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.576672191879865e-29, \"text\": \"Maasai\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These weakened the Maasai and made it easier to push them out of their traditional grazing lands to make way for settler communities and wildlife reserves.\", \"from\": 4720, \"to\": 4875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Maasai have been beaten, harassed, and even killed by police and the army.\", \"from\": 4877, \"to\": 4955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since 2009 in Tanzania, they have been subjected to excessive use of force, arbitrary arrests and detentions, and forced evictions in the Ngorongoro area.\", \"from\": 4956, \"to\": 5110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4970, \"end\": 4978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.585066202956951e-31, \"text\": \"Tanzania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\"}, {\"begin\": 5094, \"end\": 5104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngorongoro_Conservation_Area\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.9268260551432406e-17, \"text\": \"Ngorongoro\", \"types\": [\"Q473972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngorongoro_Conservation_Area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngorongoro_Conservation_Area\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Kenya, they have been ravaged by drought and famine, and their herds nearly wiped out.\", \"from\": 5112, \"to\": 5201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5115, \"end\": 5120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.513475844985777e-23, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But they have managed to maintain their culture and way of life through all the obstacles.\", \"from\": 5202, \"to\": 5292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Few African people have so stubbornly refused to die.\", \"from\": 5293, \"to\": 5346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5297, \"end\": 5311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demographics_of_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"African people\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demographics_of_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demographics_of_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Who would not want a piece of that?\", \"from\": 5348, \"to\": 5383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The author is a journalist, writer, and curator of the \\\"Wall of Great Africans\\\".\", \"from\": 5385, \"to\": 5465, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Twitter@cobbo3    You already have a Subscription?Log in  If you have an Ad-blocker please disable it and reload the page or try again later.\", \"from\": 5466, \"to\": 5607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nation Media Group \\u00a9 2025\", \"from\": 5609, \"to\": 5634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5609, \"end\": 5627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nation_Media_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nation Media Group\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nation_Media_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nation_Media_Group\"}]}]}"